  "title": "Credit Control Manager",
  "description": "<p>* Evaluate credit applications and perform credit checks on new and existing customers.<br />* Manage and liaise with credit insurance to ensure customers' credit limits in place<br />* Assess and prepare internal approvals for credit limits when necessary<br />* Conduct credit risk analysis and regularly review customer portfolios to minimize bad debt and optimize<br />   receivables<br />* Handle disputes and negotiate payment arrangements with delinquent customers to recover outstanding <br />   debts<br />* Ensure credit control processes and procedures are in compliance with company standards and polices<br />* Supervise the credit control team and work closely with clients and internal business units to resolve dispute<br />* Timely collections and reduce exposure to potential bad debt<br />* Recommends to stop delivery to customers who fail to pay promptly<br />* Recommends to take legal action against problematic customers<br />* Update the management any credit related development in order to mitigate the credit risk<br />* Degree or Diploma in Business / Commerce or related field<br />* Minimum 8 years of experience in a similar function and 3-5 years of managerial experience<br />* Strong understanding of credit control policies, contact and business law<br />* Knowledgeable about current economic outlook and situation and kept abreast of overall market credit<br />   performance<br />* Excellent interpersonal and negotiation skills<br />* 5 days work week<br />* Transport provided ant Woodlands and Jurong East MRT station</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 8,
